\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {2}{\ignorespaces Comprehensive Performance Dashboard (all errors in mHz; $N=30$ MC). \textbf  {(a)}~Time-domain frequency error, Scenario~D (Composite Islanding): event-gating in RA-EKF limits $T_{\mathrm  {trip}}$ to ${\approx }0.40$\,ms vs.\ 122\,ms for standard EKF. \textbf  {(b)}~Time-domain frequency error, Scenario~B (Ramp): RA-EKF lowest RMSE among evaluated estimators ($8.23$\,mHz) via explicit $\dot  {\omega }$ state; IpDFT at 2-cycle window has 33\,ms structural latency (observation delay, not stochastic lag) and achieves RMSE\,$=35$\,mHz; SOGI-FLL fails ($1120$\,mHz) due to type-1 loop. \textbf  {(c)}~Time-domain, Scenario~E: stable estimators. \textbf  {(d)}~Time-domain, Scenario~E: unstable estimators (TKEO excluded, RMSE\,$\geq 7800$\,mHz). \textbf  {(e)}~Pareto frontier: CPU time/sample vs.\ $T_{\mathrm  {trip}}$, Scenario~E; 2D projection only---RMSE is a third independent dimension not shown here. $\dagger $PI-GRU excluded (CPU\,${\approx }154$\,ms/sample, $T_{\mathrm  {trip}}\!\approx \!3.8$\,s). All CPU values are Python baselines; embedded speedups of 10--100$\times $ expected with C/FPGA implementations. \textbf  {(f)}~Radar chart: normalised multi-metric profile per estimator (lower area = better overall balance across all metrics). \textbf  {(g)}~Non-normative compliance heatmap, all scenarios. Pass thresholds: RMSE\,$<0.05$\,Hz, Peak\,$<0.5$\,Hz, $T_{\mathrm  {trip}}<0.1$\,s (from IEC/IEEE~60255-118-1 accuracy classes; visualisation only, no certification claim). \textbf  {F*}\,=\,marginal failure: RMSE overshoot $<1.5\%$ or sub-cycle peak breach only, compliant in all other metrics. RA-EKF, Scenario~D: peak\,$=365$\,mHz, $T_{\mathrm  {trip}}\!=\!0$. \textbf  {(h)}~Steady-state RMSE, log scale, Scenario~C (Modulation); all values $<1$\,mHz for top-performing estimators.}}{6}{figure.caption.7}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:dashboard_mega}{{2}{6}{Comprehensive Performance Dashboard (all errors in mHz; $N=30$ MC). \textbf {(a)}~Time-domain frequency error, Scenario~D (Composite Islanding): event-gating in RA-EKF limits $T_{\mathrm {trip}}$ to ${\approx }0.40$\,ms vs.\ 122\,ms for standard EKF. \textbf {(b)}~Time-domain frequency error, Scenario~B (Ramp): RA-EKF lowest RMSE among evaluated estimators ($8.23$\,mHz) via explicit $\dot {\omega }$ state; IpDFT at 2-cycle window has 33\,ms structural latency (observation delay, not stochastic lag) and achieves RMSE\,$=35$\,mHz; SOGI-FLL fails ($1120$\,mHz) due to type-1 loop. \textbf {(c)}~Time-domain, Scenario~E: stable estimators. \textbf {(d)}~Time-domain, Scenario~E: unstable estimators (TKEO excluded, RMSE\,$\geq 7800$\,mHz). \textbf {(e)}~Pareto frontier: CPU time/sample vs.\ $T_{\mathrm {trip}}$, Scenario~E; 2D projection only---RMSE is a third independent dimension not shown here. $\dagger $PI-GRU excluded (CPU\,${\approx }154$\,ms/sample, $T_{\mathrm {trip}}\!\approx \!3.8$\,s). All CPU values are Python baselines; embedded speedups of 10--100$\times $ expected with C/FPGA implementations. \textbf {(f)}~Radar chart: normalised multi-metric profile per estimator (lower area = better overall balance across all metrics). \textbf {(g)}~Non-normative compliance heatmap, all scenarios. Pass thresholds: RMSE\,$<0.05$\,Hz, Peak\,$<0.5$\,Hz, $T_{\mathrm {trip}}<0.1$\,s (from IEC/IEEE~60255-118-1 accuracy classes; visualisation only, no certification claim). \textbf {F*}\,=\,marginal failure: RMSE overshoot $<1.5\%$ or sub-cycle peak breach only, compliant in all other metrics. RA-EKF, Scenario~D: peak\,$=365$\,mHz, $T_{\mathrm {trip}}\!=\!0$. \textbf {(h)}~Steady-state RMSE, log scale, Scenario~C (Modulation); all values $<1$\,mHz for top-performing estimators}{figure.caption.7}{}}
